---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ClockChangeCountdown from '../components/ClockChangeCountdown.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Clock Change Countdown — When Do the Clocks Go Forward or Back? | Clockr"
	description="Live countdown to the next daylight saving time change. Find out when clocks go forward or back in the UK, US, or EU."
	category="seasons"
>
	<div class="sc-page">
		<div class="sc-header">
			<div class="sc-eyebrow">
				<span class="sc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				SEASONS
			</div>
			<h1 class="sc-title">
				<span class="sc-gradient">Clock Change Countdown</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="sc-subtitle">Find out when the clocks go forward or back</p>
		</div>

		<ClockChangeCountdown client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="sc-how">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="sc-how-card">
				<p>
					Daylight Saving Time (DST) shifts clocks forward by one hour in spring
					and back by one hour in autumn. The idea, first widely adopted during
					the First World War, was to make better use of natural daylight —
					moving an hour of sunlight from early morning to the evening so people
					use less artificial lighting and can enjoy lighter evenings after work.
					Many countries still observe DST today, though the practice remains
					controversial.
				</p>
				<p>
					Clock change dates are not the same everywhere. In the UK and EU,
					clocks go forward on the last Sunday in March and back on the last
					Sunday in October. The United States follows a different schedule:
					clocks spring forward on the second Sunday in March and fall back on
					the first Sunday in November. This page calculates those dates
					dynamically for each year — no hardcoded calendar entries — so the
					countdown always points to the correct upcoming change for your
					selected region.
				</p>
				<p>
					Whether DST should continue is actively debated. The European
					Parliament voted in 2019 to abolish seasonal clock changes, but
					implementation has been delayed and most EU member states still
					observe DST as of 2026. In the US, the Sunshine Protection Act —
					which would make daylight saving time permanent — has been discussed in
					Congress but has not become federal law. Some US states and countries
					worldwide have already opted out of DST entirely.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="sc-faq">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="sc-faq-list">
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>When do the clocks go forward in the UK?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							In the UK, clocks go forward one hour to British Summer Time (BST)
							on the last Sunday in March, at 1:00am. At that moment, 1:00am
							becomes 2:00am. The exact date changes each year depending on
							which Sunday falls last in March — use the countdown above for the
							precise date and live timer.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>When do the clocks go back in the UK?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							UK clocks go back one hour to Greenwich Mean Time (GMT) on the
							last Sunday in October, at 2:00am. At that moment, 2:00am becomes
							1:00am, giving you an extra hour in bed. The date varies slightly
							by year; the countdown above shows the next occurrence.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Do the US and UK change clocks on the same date?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							No. The UK and EU change clocks on the last Sunday in March and
							the last Sunday in October. The United States uses different
							dates: the second Sunday in March (spring forward) and the first
							Sunday in November (fall back). That means US and UK clock changes
							are often a week or more apart. Select your region in the toggle
							above to see the correct dates.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Which countries don't observe Daylight Saving Time?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Many countries near the equator do not use DST because daylight
							length barely changes through the year. Japan, India, China, and
							most of Africa do not observe it. Within the US, Arizona (except
							the Navajo Nation) and Hawaii stay on standard time year-round.
							Russia abolished seasonal clock changes in 2014. Turkey also
							keeps a fixed offset year-round.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">Why do we change the clocks?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Clocks are changed to shift an hour of daylight from the morning
							to the evening during the longer days of summer. Proponents argue
							this saves energy, reduces road accidents in lighter evenings, and
							boosts outdoor leisure and retail. Critics point to disrupted
							sleep, health effects, and questionable energy savings in the
							modern era. The original motivation was wartime fuel conservation.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Is the UK going to stop changing the clocks?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							There is no confirmed plan to end clock changes in the UK as of
							2026. The EU voted to abolish seasonal changes, which prompted UK
							debate, but Brexit means the UK sets its own policy independently.
							Any change would require legislation and coordination with
							neighbouring countries — especially Ireland, which shares a land
							border with Northern Ireland.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="sc-related">
			<h3 class="sc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="sc-related-grid">
				<a href="/season-countdown" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Season Countdown</span></a
				>
				<a href="/utc-gmt-converter" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">UTC/GMT Converter</span></a
				>
				<a href="/world-clock" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">World Clock</span></a
				>
				<a href="/time-zone-meeting-planner" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Time Zone Meeting Planner</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.sc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.sc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.sc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.sc-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-hero-band {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 100vw;
		margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
		padding: 48px 24px 56px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d1f17, #1a2e24);
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		overflow: hidden;
		position: relative;
	}

	.sc-hero-decor {
		position: absolute;
		inset: 0;
		pointer-events: none;
		user-select: none;
	}

	.sc-float-emoji {
		position: absolute;
		display: inline-block;
		line-height: 1;
		transform: rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		animation: sc-float 4s ease-in-out infinite;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.sc-float-emoji {
			opacity: 0.35;
		}
	}

	@keyframes sc-float {
		0%,
		100% {
			transform: translateY(0) rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		}
		33% {
			transform: translateY(-10px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) - 3deg));
		}
		66% {
			transform: translateY(-5px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) + 3deg));
		}
	}

	.sc-hero-centre {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 720px;
	}

	.ccc-region-wrap {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		margin-bottom: 28px;
		width: 100%;
	}

	.ccc-region-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 2px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
	}

	.ccc-region-toggle {
		display: flex;
		gap: 8px;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		justify-content: center;
	}

	.ccc-region-btn {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		padding: 10px 24px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.35);
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.6);
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease,
			color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.ccc-region-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.5);
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
	}

	.ccc-region-btn--active {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.7);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.2);
		color: #fff;
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.2);
	}

	.ccc-direction {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(20px, 4vw, 28px);
		font-weight: 800;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		margin: 0 0 24px;
		padding: 10px 24px;
		border-radius: 12px;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}

	.ccc-direction--forward {
		color: #fbbf24;
		background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.12);
		border: 1px solid rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.35);
		text-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.3);
	}

	.ccc-direction--back {
		color: #60a5fa;
		background: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.12);
		border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.35);
		text-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.3);
	}

	.sc-countdown {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-end;
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px 12px;
	}

	.sc-countdown-block {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.sc-countdown-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		min-width: 64px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.sc-countdown-num--days {
		font-size: clamp(80px, 13vw, 120px);
		letter-spacing: -4px;
		min-width: 100px;
	}

	.sc-countdown-sep {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: 26px;
		padding: 0 2px;
	}

	.sc-countdown-unit {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 2px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
	}

	.sc-target-date {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(15px, 2.5vw, 18px);
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin: 28px 0 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.ccc-following {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		margin: 10px 0 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
		max-width: 520px;
	}

	.sc-note {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 16px 0 0;
		max-width: 520px;
	}

	.sc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.sc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.sc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.sc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-item[open] .sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.sc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.sc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.sc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.sc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.sc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.sc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.4);
	}

	.sc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.sc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.sc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
